"a.稳定的，不变的; n.常数 【英】 adj. 稳定的, 不变的(unchanging);n. 常数(invariable) 【考】 craven : heroic / volatile : constant(懦弱的不英勇/易变 的不稳定)fickle : constancy / naive : sophistication(易变的不恒定/纯真 的不世故)反义词：mercurial( 易变的); intermittent(间断的) 【记】 con(始终)+stant(站, 立) →始终站立→不变的 【同】 派生词: constancy (n. 恒定不变); constantly (adv.不断地frequent ly) adj. 持续不断的 = persistent; 稳定不变的; n 常数 = invariable 【记】con全部, stant站－我们在痛苦的军训过程中站军姿的时候－不变的 【参】constantly(adv 不变地; 经常地; 坚持不懈地 = frequently) 【类】craven: heroic = volatile: constant懦弱的不英勇的 = 易变的不稳定的 【反】mercurial(adj 水星的; 活泼善变的; 水银的); intermittent(adj 间歇的; 断断续续的) 【记】源自stand，con + stand 大家一起站立着，非常坚定，心不变 constant (adj.)  late 14c., ""steadfast, resolute,"" from Old French constant (14c.) or directly from Latin constantem (nominative constans) ""standing firm, stable, steadfast, faithful,"" present participle of constare, from com- ""together"" (see com-) + stare ""to stand,"" from PIE root *sta- ""to stand"" (see stet). Of actions and conditions from 1650s. Related: Constantly. constant (n.)  1832 in mathematics and physics, from constant (adj.)."
